  <slide>
    <title>MAIN Landmark Design Patterns</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li>Typically one <code>main</code> landmark per page</li>
        <li>Each <code>main</code> landmark has a <code>h1</code> element</li>
        <li>If more than one <code>h1</code> element and <code>main</code> landmarks use <code>aria-labelledby</code> for naming the <code>main</code> landmark</li>
      </ul>

  <h2>One Main Landmark</h2>

      <p class="code">
        &lt;div <strong>role="main"&gt;</strong><br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;h1&gt;<em>title for main content</em>&lt;h1&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;.... <em>main content</em>....   <br/><br/>
        &lt;/div&gt;
      </p>


      <h2>Multiple Main Landmarks</h2>

      <p class="code">
        &lt;div <strong>role="main"  aria-labelledby="<em>title1</em>"</strong>&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;h1 <strong>id="<em>title1</em>"</strong>&gt;<em>title for main content 1</em>&lt;h1&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;.... <em>main content</em>....   <br/><br/>
        &lt;/div&gt;
        ....
        &lt;div <strong>role="main"  aria-labelledby="<em>title2</em>"</strong>&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;h1 <strong>id="<em>title2</em>"</strong>&gt;<em>title for main content 2</em>&lt;h1&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;.... <em>main content</em>....   <br/><br/>
        &lt;/div&gt;
      </p>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>NAVIGATION Landmark Design Patterns</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li>Use <code>navigation</code> landmark on a element <em>containing</em> the list and <code>h2</code> element</li>
        <li>Each <code>navigation</code> landmark should have a <code>h2</code> element before the list of links</li>
        <li>If there is more than one <code>navigation</code> landmark use <code>aria-labelledby</code> for labeling the landmark with the <code>h2</code> element</li>
        <li>Use <code>ul</code> element and <code>li</code> elements for the list of links in the navigation bar</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>One <code>navigation</code> landmark</h2>
      <p class="code">
        &lt;div <strong>role="navigation"</strong>&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;h2&gt;<em>title for navigation</em>&lt;h2&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;ul><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page1.html"&gt;Link 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page2.html"&gt;Link 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page3.html"&gt;Link 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page4.html"&gt;Link 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;.....<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;/ul><br/>
        &lt;/div&gt;
      </p>
      <h2>More than one <code>navigation</code> landmark</h2>
      <p class="code">
        &lt;div <strong>role="navigation"  aria-labelledby="<em>nav1</em>"</strong>&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;h2 <strong>id="<em>nav1</em>"</strong>&gt;<em>title for navigation 1</em>&lt;h2&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;ul><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page11.html"&gt;Link 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page12.html"&gt;Link 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page13.html"&gt;Link 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page14.html"&gt;Link 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;.....<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;/ul><br/>
        &lt;/div&gt;<br/>
        &lt;div <strong>role="navigation"  aria-labelledby="<em>nav2</em>"</strong>&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;h2 <strong>id="<em>nav2</em>"</strong>&gt;<em>title for navigation 2</em>&lt;h2&gt;<br/><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;ul><br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page21.html"&gt;Page 10&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page22.html"&gt;Page 11&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page23.html"&gt;Page 12&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="page24.html"&gt;Page 13&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;.....<br/>
        &#160;&#160;&lt;/ul><br/>
        &lt;/div&gt;
      </p>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Landmark Design Patterns</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li>All content should be contained in a landmark:
          <ul>
            <li>banner</li>
            <li>complementary</li>
            <li>contentinfo</li>
            <li>main</li>
            <li>navigation</li>
            <li>search</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><em>Should</em> use labels with all landmarks</li>
        <li><em>Must</em> use labels when a landmark of the same type is used more than once</li>
        <li><em>Should</em> not nest landmarks of the same type</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Use of Headings (H1-H6) in ARIA Landmarks</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li><code>main</code> landmarks should contain <code>h1</code> element at the beginning of section:
          <ul>
            <li><code>h1</code> element content describes the content or the purpose of the page</li>
            <li>Provides a redundent means for assistive technology users to navigate to main content</li>
            <li>Use headers in a structural way or in combination with HTML5 section elements</li>
            <li>If more than one <code>main</code> landmark on the page use <code>aria-labelledby</code> to use the heading as accessible name to the landmark</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><code>navigation</code> and <code>complementary </code>landmarks should contain <code>h2</code> element at the beginning of section:
          <ul>
            <li><code>h2</code> element content describes the content or the purpose of the page</li>
            <li>Provides a redundent means for assistive technology users to navigate to content</li>
            <li>If more than one <code>navigation</code> or <code>complementary </code> landmark on the page use <code>aria-labelledby</code> to use the heading as accessible name for each landmark</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><code>contentinfo</code> landmark should contain <code>h3</code> element at the beginning of section:
          <ul>
            <li><code>h3</code> element identifies the section as footer information</li>
            <li>Provides a redundent means for assistive technology users to navigate to content</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

